kind: llman.sdd.spec
name: "sdd-ison-authoring"
purpose: "TBD - created by archiving change migrate-llmanspec-specs-to-ison-table. Update Purpose after archive."
valid_scope[2]: src/,tests/
requirements[7]{req_id,title,statement}:
  r1,Canonical Table ISON Schema for Main Specs,"ÕĮō `llmanspec/config.yaml` ÕŻ░µśÄ `spec_style: ison` µŚČ’╝ī`llmanspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md` MUST embed canonical semantic content using table/object ISON inside one or more fenced ` ```ison ` code blocks. The ISON payload MUST provide these blocks with strictly fixed names and columns: - `object.spec` (exactly 1 row): `kind name purpose` - `table.requirements`: `req_id title statement` - `table.scenarios`: `req_id id given when then` Validation MUST enforce: - `object.spec.kind` equals `llman.sdd.s"
  r2,Canonical Table ISON Schema for Delta Specs,"ÕĮō `llmanspec/config.yaml` ÕŻ░µśÄ `spec_style: ison` µŚČ’╝ī`llmanspec/changes/<change-id>/specs/<capability>/spec.md` MUST embed delta semantics using table/object ISON inside one or more fenced ` ```ison ` code blocks. The ISON payload MUST provide these blocks with strictly fixed names and columns: - `object.delta` (exactly 1 row): `kind` (kind = `llman.sdd.delta`) - `table.ops`: `op req_id title statement from to name` - `table.op_scenarios`: `req_id id given when then` Validation MUST enforce: - `obj"
  r3,Multiple ISON Blocks Are Supported and Merged by Canonical Block Name,"ÕĮō `llmanspec/config.yaml` ÕŻ░µśÄ `spec_style: ison` µŚČ’╝īspec and delta files MUST be allowed to split the required canonical blocks across multiple fenced ` ```ison ` code blocks (for example, one ISON block per Markdown section). The runtime MUST: - extract all ` ```ison ` code blocks from the file, - parse each payload (table/object ISON), - merge blocks by block name into a single semantic document, - fail validation when a required canonical block is missing, - fail validation when any canonical b"
  r4,"Token-Friendly Dumps Are the Default and Deterministic","All llman commands that write or rewrite spec payloads (CRUD edits, archive merge outputs, conversions) MUST emit deterministic dumps for the configured style. - In `ison` projects, the default dump MUST remain token-friendly (no column-alignment padding). - In `ison` projects, the CLI MAY provide opt-in pretty alignment for review. - In `toon` and `yaml` projects, the serializer MUST use stable field ordering, stable list ordering, and consistent indentation. Repeated writes without semantic ch"
  r5,CLI Provides Authoring Helpers for Skeletons and Delta CRUD,"The SDD CLI MUST provide first-class authoring helpers that emit the projectŌĆÖs configured style for: - create/update a main spec skeleton for a capability - create/update a delta spec skeleton for a change + capability - add/modify/remove/rename a requirement op in a delta spec - add a scenario to a spec or delta op If the project has no declared `spec_style`, these authoring helpers MUST fail loudly instead of silently choosing a format. Style-specific formatting flags MUST also be enforced str"
  r6,TOON õĖÄ YAML õĖ╗ spec õĮ┐ńö©ń╗¤õĖĆÕ»╣Ķ▒ĪĶ»Łõ╣ē,"ÕĮō `llmanspec/config.yaml` ÕŻ░µśÄ `spec_style: toon` µł¢ `spec_style: yaml` µŚČ’╝ī`llmanspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md` MUST Õ£©õĖÄķŻÄµĀ╝Õī╣ķģŹńÜä fenced block õĖŁµē┐ĶĮĮõĖĆõĖ¬ canonical µ¢ćµĪŻÕ»╣Ķ▒ĪŃĆé ķŻÄµĀ╝õĖÄ fence ńÜäÕ»╣Õ║öÕģ│ń│╗ MUST õĖ║’╝Ü - `toon` ŌåÆ ` ```toon ` - `yaml` ŌåÆ ` ```yaml ` Ķ»ź canonical µ¢ćµĪŻ MUST ĶĪ©ĶŠŠõ╗źõĖŗõĖ╗ spec Ķ»Łõ╣ēÕŁŚµ«Ą’╝Ü - `kind` - `name` - `purpose` - `requirements` - `scenarios` ÕģČõĖŁ’╝Ü - `kind` MUST ńŁēõ║Ä `llman.sdd.spec` - `name` Õ£© strict µ©ĪÕ╝ÅõĖŗ MUST ńŁēõ║Ä `<capability>` - `requirements` õĖŁńÜäµ»ÅõĖĆķĪ╣ MUST ÕīģÕÉ½ `req_id`ŃĆü`title`ŃĆü`statement` - `scenarios` õĖŁńÜäµ»ÅõĖĆķĪ╣ MUST ÕīģÕÉ½ `re"
  r7,TOON õĖÄ YAML delta spec õĮ┐ńö©ń╗¤õĖĆ ops Ķ»Łõ╣ē,"ÕĮō `llmanspec/config.yaml` ÕŻ░µśÄ `spec_style: toon` µł¢ `spec_style: yaml` µŚČ’╝ī`llmanspec/changes/<change-id>/specs/<capability>/spec.md` MUST Õ£©õĖÄķŻÄµĀ╝Õī╣ķģŹńÜä fenced block õĖŁµē┐ĶĮĮõĖĆõĖ¬ canonical delta µ¢ćµĪŻÕ»╣Ķ▒ĪŃĆé Ķ»źÕ»╣Ķ▒Ī MUST ĶĪ©ĶŠŠõ╗źõĖŗÕŁŚµ«Ą’╝Ü - `kind` - `ops` - `op_scenarios` ÕģČõĖŁ’╝Ü - `kind` MUST ńŁēõ║Ä `llman.sdd.delta` - `ops` õĖŁńÜäµ»ÅõĖĆķĪ╣ MUST õĮ┐ńö©ÕŁŚµ«Ą `op`ŃĆü`req_id`ŃĆü`title`ŃĆü`statement`ŃĆü`from`ŃĆü`to`ŃĆü`name` - `op_scenarios` õĖŁńÜäµ»ÅõĖĆķĪ╣ MUST õĮ┐ńö©ÕŁŚµ«Ą `req_id`ŃĆü`id`ŃĆü`given`ŃĆü`when`ŃĆü`then` - `op` MUST µś» `add_requirement`ŃĆü`modify_requirement`ŃĆü`remove_requirement`ŃĆü`renam"
scenarios[9]{req_id,id,given,when,then}:
  r1,"canonical-blocks-can-be-parsed-without-depending-on-markdown","",a main spec in an `ison` project contains Markdown headings/prose plus the required ` ```ison ` blocks,the runtime extracts and parses the ISON blocks as the canonical semantic source
  r2,"delta-ops-and-scenarios-are-representable-as-deterministic-t","",an `ison` project contains an add/modify/remove/rename requirement delta spec,the delta operations are represented as rows in `table.ops`
  r3,"canonical-blocks-can-be-split-across-sections","","an `ison` spec file places `object.spec`, `table.requirements`, and `table.scenarios` in separate ` ```ison ` blocks under different Markdown headings",the runtime merges them and produces the same semantic result as a single combined ISON block
  r4,"repeated-yaml-writes-do-not-churn-formatting","","a maintainer runs the same YAML-targeted write command twice without source changes","the emitted ` ```yaml ` payload text is byte-identical across runs"
  r5,"maintainer-can-author-a-yaml-delta-spec-without-manual-forma","",a maintainer in a `yaml` project uses CLI authoring helpers to create a delta spec skeleton and add an `add_requirement` op plus a scenario,the resulting file is written in ` ```yaml ` format
  r6,"yaml-õĖ╗-spec-µ╗ĪĶČ│ń╗¤õĖĆÕ»╣Ķ▒ĪĶ»Łõ╣ē","","ķĪ╣ńø«ÕŻ░µśÄ `spec_style: yaml`",Ķ┐ÉĶĪīµŚČÕÅ»Õ░åÕģČĶ¦Żµ×ÉõĖ║õĖ╗ spec Ķ»Łõ╣ēÕ»╣Ķ▒Ī
